<subSubSection id="3FC68BD30469332857CE05EBBB1765E4" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="90606F7463ABC29B889BCE270BFB2DC3" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6364EBC195B4B1A6D16D0BEABC0884B" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">
<bibRefCitation id="41DDF765896408559DE8DD3A75ABFF10" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="303 - 319" publicationUrl="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, 1936. The Brazilian species of Selaginella. Feddes Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 40: 303 - 319, DOI: 10.1002/fedr.19360402005" title="The Brazilian species of Selaginella." url="10.1002/fedr.19360402005" volume="40" year="1936">Alston (1936)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A208B66FC1432318E07329FE9A64DA48" author="Reed, CF" journalOrPublisher="Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana" pageId="20" pageNumber="113" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B21" refString="Reed, CF, 1965-1966. Index Selaginellarum. Memorias da Sociedade Broteriana 18: 1 - 287" title="Index Selaginellarum." volume="18" year="1965 - 1966">Reed (1965-1966)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="E1A59A83E0D2C2C593B2D8F7DC24A5F7" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="5E5CC23C5FE6D12AB9C2EEB99EF0126F" authorityName="Hieron" authorityYear="1904" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella glazioviana" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">
<emphasis id="842F1C0A6A4ABC7882649A46F1FE47C5" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella glazioviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="D1B264BC094020270F61FC0A25D6E28A" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella erectifolia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="erectifolia">
<emphasis id="1C51016008DDD27CD60C4840FAEE0DB3" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella erectifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have studied type material of 
<taxonomicName id="E43F820F801B84D67DE7DCAF4386D52B" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella erectifolia" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="erectifolia">
<emphasis id="C9598E45D677DE9DDB6FA941CB755AC2" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella erectifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="C0843B0CA6E515E525E112578BB44234" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Swainson s.n.</emphasis>
, holotype: K!) and its synonym 
<taxonomicName id="9A1F011231A06E680A7422BA661FA668" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella camptostachys" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="camptostachys">
<emphasis id="3B1241842610B372256BD528B8F88737" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella camptostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="43C4035EC09184516DE3A34D3F7B3B90" originalValue="Fée">Fee</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="E95A28195F6F227EDD823F2424D469E9" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Glaziou 2242</emphasis>
, holotype: P!; isotypes: B!, BR!, K!, NY-fragment!) and agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="E5AEE168F26BB0BA2E0F463C81DF5E52" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
that they are conspecific, but I consider 
<taxonomicName id="56BAEC3D55938B027DF7EBF33ADF9F19" authorityName="Hieron" authorityYear="1904" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella glazioviana" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">
<emphasis id="42356985DB8A0EDDD55E45CEF8F3B46E" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella glazioviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a different species. A full account of that finding, along with the formal resurrection of 
<taxonomicName id="F067FADA3E19BCEC57EA344967F348CF" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella deltoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="deltoides">
<emphasis id="383939806198439D06CC9F7497424C63" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella deltoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="08DB135625FF63D961304F25E5553E5E" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1898" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella chromatophylla" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="chromatophylla">
<emphasis id="9F46CD5BC593CFDBF46638A45134953E" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella chromatophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, will be reported separately (Valdespino in prep). 
<taxonomicName id="23A9484DFBCB63F2C7AF0FC375D77BA2" authorityName="Hieron" authorityYear="1904" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella glazioviana" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">
<emphasis id="74D705C7A4D0056B443BBF19559C4AC9" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella glazioviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="5D0B15E25876AA0ACE2E2056AC5769E8" authorityName="Valdespino" authorityYear="2015" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella trygonoides" order="Selaginellales" pageId="16" pageNumber="109" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="trygonoides">
<emphasis id="D36ABCF123A1E1806FCB615690D84286" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="109">Selaginella trygonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described herein (see for comparison).
</paragraph>
